`scripts/` is the collection of standalone CI/lint checks and doc-generators that back `ctx-verify` and repo hygiene — each script is independently invocable, emits `FAIL: path:line: ...` lines to stderr in a shared format, and returns nonzero on failure. Depending on this directory gets you a set of checks whose exit codes and `FAIL:` output ctx-verify parses uniformly; nothing here is a library, each file is a standalone entrypoint.

The shared protocol binds most children together: enumerate files via `git ls-files -z --cached --others --exclude-standard` (never a raw filesystem walk, to avoid races with `target/` writers and to respect `.gitignore`), force `/dev/null` into grep's arg list so `file:line:` prefixes always appear even for single-file matches, and print `FAIL: ` lines to stderr while accumulating a `FAIL` flag rather than short-circuiting on the first hit. `no_allow_check.sh`, `retired_terms_check.sh`, and `workspace_lints_check.sh` all follow this exact pattern; changing the output format in one likely means updating the others plus ctx-verify's parser (`split_loc`) in lockstep.

Two scripts (`cycle_check.sh`, `machete_check.sh`) instead wrap external cargo subcommands (`cargo-modules`, `cargo-machete`) and treat a missing binary as a hard failure with an install hint, deliberately not degrading silently — `cycle_check.sh` is also explicitly a placeholder (no real cycle detection yet, deferred to a future dylint rule) while `rationale_check.py` is a similar MVP placeholder for size/complexity linting, using brace-balance heuristics rather than an AST.

`gen_readme_architecture.sh` and `gen_tool_contracts.sh` are the doc-generation half: both support `--write`/`--check` against marker-delimited blocks in README.md (and CLAUDE.md for the latter), both hard-fail if markers are missing, and both are the only things allowed to touch those generated blocks — never hand-edit between the markers. `gen_tool_contracts.sh` requires six `target/debug/` binaries to already be built (never invokes cargo itself); `gen_readme_architecture.sh` requires `.context/rollup.ctx` to exist as a pre-generated artifact.

No intent.md exists for this directory.